===Retired numbers===
{{See also|List of Major League Baseball retired numbers}}
The Padres have retired five numbers.  Four were in honor of Padre players and one was Jackie Robinson's number 42, which was retired by all of Major League Baseball. 

{| class="wikitable" style="font-style:bold; font-size:120%; border:3px;"
|-  style="text-align:center; background:white;"
|[[Image:PadresRetired6.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Steve Garvey|Steve<br />Garvey]]<br />1B<br /><font size=1>Retired 1989</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetired19.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Tony Gwynn|Tony<br />Gwynn]]<br />RF<br /><font size=1>Retired 2004</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetired31.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Dave Winfield|Dave<br />Winfield]]<br />RF<br /><font size=1>Retired 2001</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetired35.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Randy Jones (baseball)|Randy<br />Jones]]<br />P<br /><font size=1>Retired 1997</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetiredJC.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Jerry Coleman|Jerry<br />Coleman]]<br />Broadcaster<br /><font size=1>Honored 2004</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetiredRK.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Ray Kroc|Ray<br />Kroc]]<br />Owner<br /><font size=1>Honored 2004</font>'''
|[[Image:PadresRetired42.png|95px|]]<br />'''[[Jackie Robinson|Jackie<br />Robinson]]<br />-<br /><font size=1>Retired 1997</font>'''
|}

The retired numbers are displayed in center field atop the batter's eye wall.  They are free standing and mounted on poles.  During the 2004 season, the first season in PETCO Park, there were only four retired numbers displayed.  Gwynn's number 19 was not yet officially retired until late in the season and was added the following winter. It was announced that [[Trevor Hoffman|Trevor Hoffman's]] number 51 would be retired on August 21, 2011. <ref>http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20110616&content_id=20577792&vkey=news_mlb&c_id=mlb</ref>

The Padres also have a "star on the wall" in honor of broadcaster [[Jerry Coleman]], in reference to his trademark phrase "Oh Doctor! You can hang a star on that baby!"  Nearby the initials of former owner [[Ray Kroc]] are also displayed.  Both the star and the initials are painted in gold on the front of the pressbox down the right field line accompanied by the name of the person in white.

===Team Hall of Fame===
People inducted into the San Diego Padres Team Hall of Fame which was founded in 1999.

*[[Buzzie Bavasi]], Team President, 1969<U+2013>1977. Inducted 2001.
*[[Nate Colbert]], 1B, 1969<U+2013>1974. Inducted 1999.
*[[Jerry Coleman]], Manager, 1980, Announcer, 1972<U+2013>1979, 1981<U+2013>present. Inducted 2001.
*[[Tony Gwynn]], OF, 1982<U+2013>2002. Inducted 2007.
*[[Randy Jones (baseball)|Randy Jones]], P, 1973<U+2013>1980. Inducted 1999.
*[[Ray Kroc]], Owner, 1974<U+2013>1984. Inducted 1999.
*[[Dick Williams]], Manager, 1982<U+2013>1985. Inducted 2009.
*[[Dave Winfield]], OF, 1973<U+2013>1980. Inducted 2000.

